The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for solving the Hamiltonian cycle problem, which are topics that fall under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), as the paper focuses on the properties of graphs and their Hamiltonian cycles. The next likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes an improved backtrack algorithm with sophisticated pruning techniques. The paper also touches on computational complexity, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The topics of graph drawing and visualization are briefly mentioned, which could place the paper under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of regular graphs, which could place it under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
